  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators have conducted a prospective, double-blind, randomized study to assess the
      comparative safety and efficacy of two different ablation strategies, RFA versus RFA plus
      botulinum toxin injection, in patients with supra-ventricular tachyarrhythmias. Results were
      assessed with the use of an implanted monitoring device (IMD).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
